AstraX –  Terms of Service THIS VERSION IS IN MAINTENANCE / IS NOT THE FULL VERSION SOME THING MAY BE OFF!!!

1. Introduction

Welcome to AstraX, a multifunctional Discord bot providing moderation, utility, and automation features.
By adding or using AstraX in your server, you agree to all Terms outlined in this document.

AstraX is developed and managed by the development team.
(You can find that team in official Discord Support Server)

Support Server: https://discord.gg/VWeUYWcmm6



2. Eligibility

To use AstraX, you must:

Be at least 13 years old (Discord ToS requirement | https://support.discord.com/hc/en-us/articles/360040724612-Why-is-Discord-asking-for-my-birthday)

Follow Discord’s Terms of Service and Community Guidelines



3. Features Covered by This ToS

AstraX provides the following major features (not limited to):

Moderation

!ban, !kick, !mute, !unmute, !purge, !roleadd, !roleremove, !temprole, !unban

Configuration

!setlogs, !setautorole, !setprefix

User Utilities

!av, !banner, !userinfo, !membercount, !serverinfo

General Tools

!help, !say, !ping, !uptime

Systems

AFK system (!afk)

Reminder system (!reminder)



4. Data Collected

AstraX collects only technical Discord identifiers needed to operate:

4.1 Required for Functionality

User display name

User name

User IDs

Server name

Server icon

Server IDs

Channel IDs

Role IDs

Message IDs

Audit logs

Invite from the server the bot has bean added to

Server configurations 

4.2 Automatically Collected

These are generated by Discord itself:

Timestamps of when commands are used

Errors for debugging

Bot performance metrics


4.3 Not Collected

AstraX does NOT collect:

IP addresses

Emails

Passwords

Payment information

Device information

Real-world personal data


AstraX is fully compliant with Discord’s developer policies.



5. How Data Is Used

Your data is used ONLY for:

Running bot commands

Saving settings between restarts

Displaying requested information

Performing moderation actions

Logging events if configured


Data is never sold, shared, or given to third parties.

Only the development team & owners can access backend data strictly for maintenance and debugging.



6. Logging Policy

If server owners enable logging using !setlogs, AstraX may store or display:

Deleted messages

Edited messages

Bans, kicks, mutes, unbans

Join & leave events

Role changes

Channel updates


Important:
AstraX logs only Discord events that are already visible to server moderators.
AstraX cannot view or log Direct Messages.



7. Abuse & Misuse

You agree NOT to:

Spam commands

Abuse moderation actions

Attempt to crash or exploit the bot

Self-bot or automate unauthorized bot usage

Use AstraX for harassment, raiding, or illegal activity

Pretend to be bot staff

Reverse engineer, copy, or decompile AstraX


AstraX owners may:

Blacklist users

Blacklist servers

Temporarily disable commands

Remove features being abused



8. Data Retention & Removal

8.1 Retention

Data is kept only as long as needed for the bot to operate.

8.2 Manual Deletion

AstraX currently does NOT include automated data removal commands.
Users may request manual removal by:

Opening a support ticket

Contacting Helper or Fabian


Data will be deleted within 72 hours.

8.3 Server Removal

When a server removes the bot:

Nonessential data is automatically deleted

Configuration data may be stored for up to 30 days unless deletion is requested



---

9. Availability

AstraX may be unavailable during:

Maintenance

Updates

Crashes

Host outages

Discord API downtime


Owners are not responsible for temporary downtime.
